River site: 1. Anderson Creek Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Anderson Creek data natural origin counts are based on seasonal counts of live spawners. No summer chum have been counted in Anderson Creek since 1984, so the stock is rated Extinct. Natural re-colonization may occur as Hood Canal summer chum stocks rebuild.

River site: 2. Big Beef Creek Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Big Beef Creek natural origin escapement estimates based on rack counts (the University of Washington maintains a rack at the mouth of Big Beef Creek, which is operated by WDFW) and live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 1.7. NORs and SORs based on marked and unmarked otolith sampling for all ages combined.

River site: 3. Big Beef Creek Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Big Beef Creek supplementation origin escapement estimates based on rack counts (the University of Washington maintains a rack at the mouth of Big Beef Creek, which is operated by WDFW) and live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 1.7. NORs and SORs based on marked and unmarked otolith sampling for all ages combined.

River site: 4. Big/Little Quilcene Summer Chum: Escapement (Proportion)
Description: Big/Little Quilcene River data are escapement estimates based on Quilcene National Fish Hatchery rack counts, live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.8 on the Big Quilcene River, and on Little Quilcene River live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 1.8.

River site: 5. Big/Little Quilcene Summer Chum: Index Hatchery Escapement
Description: Big Quilcene River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on Quilcene National Fish Hatchery rack counts and live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.8 in the Big Quilcene River.

River site: 6. Big/Little Quilcene Summer Chum: Index Hatchery Escapement
Description: Little Quilcene River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 1.8 in the Little Quilcene River.

River site: 7. Big/Little Quilcene Summer Chum: Index Natural Escapement
Description: Big Quilcene River natural origin escapement estimates based on Quilcene National Fish Hatchery rack counts and live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.8 in the Big Quilcene River.

River site: 8. Big/Little Quilcene Summer Chum: Index Natural Escapement
Description: Little Quilcene River natural origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 1.8 in the Little Quilcene River.

River site: 9. Dewatto Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Dewatto River supplementation origin escapements based on peak live spawner counts from RM 0.3 to 1.8 in the Dewatto River.

River site: 10. Dewatto Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Dewatto River natural origin escapements based on peak live spawner counts from RM 0.3 to 1.8 in the Dewatto River.

River site: 11. Dosewallips Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Dosewallips River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.3 in the Dosewallips River.

River site: 12. Dosewallips Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Dosewallips River natural origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.3 in the Dosewallips River.

River site: 13. Duckabush Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Duckabush River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to RM 2.3 in the Duckabush River.

River site: 14. Duckabush Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Duckabush River natural origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to RM 2.3 in the Duckabush River.

River site: 15. Finch Creek Summer Chum: Escapement (Proportion)
Description: Finch Creek data are counts of summer chum at the Hoodsport Hatchery rack. Summer chum were present when the WDFW Hoodsport Hatchery began operations in 1953 but are now extinct.

River site: 16. Hamma Hamma Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Hamma Hamma River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.3 to 1.8 in the Hamma Hamma River and in John Creek, a tributary.

River site: 17. Hamma Hamma Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Hamma Hamma River natural origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.3 to 1.8 in the Hamma Hamma River and in John Creek, a tributary.

River site: 18. Lilliwaup Creek Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Lilliwaup Creek supplementation origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 0.7 or counts of adult summer chum at a temporary trap.

River site: 19. Lilliwaup Creek Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Lilliwaup Creek natural origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 0.7 or counts of adult summer chum at a temporary trap.

River site: 20. Skokomish Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Skokomish River supplementation origin counts are based on spawning ground surveys that report an occasional summer-timed chum salmon, but the numbers are not sufficient to represent a self-sustaining stock, so the stock is rated Extinct.

River site: 21. Skokomish Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Skokomish River natural origin counts are based on spawning ground surveys that report an occasional summer-timed chum salmon, but the numbers are not sufficient to represent a self-sustaining stock, so the stock is rated Extinct.

River site: 22. Tahuya Summer Chum: Hatch-Origin Spawners (Prop.)
Description: Tahuya River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.6 in Tahuya River.

River site: 23. Tahuya Summer Chum: Natural-Origin Spawners (Prop)
Description: Tahuya River natural origin escapement estimates based on live spawner counts from RM 0.0 to 2.6 in Tahuya River.

River site: 24. Union Summer Chum: Index Hatchery Escapement
Description: Union River supplementation origin escapement estimates based on trap counts and live spawner counts from RM 0.3 to 2.1 in the Union River.

River site: 25. Union Summer Chum: Index Natural Escapement
Description: Union River natural origin escapement estimates based on trap counts and live spawner counts from RM 0.3 to 2.1 in the Union River.
